'''''Spy vs. Spy II: The Island Caper''''' is a 1985 [[video game]] developed by [[First Star Software]]. It is the sequel to ''[[Spy vs. Spy (1984 video game)|Spy vs. Spy]]''. It can be played as both [[single-player video game|single-player]] and [[multiplayer]]

==Gameplay==
[[Image:Spy vs Spy II A800 ingame.png|thumb|When in the same room, both players use the same screen, leaving the other blank.]]

''Spy vs. Spy II: The Island Caper''<ref name='atarimania2'>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-spy-vs-spy-ii_6757.html|title=Atari 400 800 XL XE Spy vs. Spy II : scans, dump, download, screenshots, ads, videos, catalog, instructions, roms|website=www.atarimania.com}}</ref> adds a side-scrolling play area.<ref name="farrell">{{cite journal|last=Farrell|first=Andrew|title=''Spy vs Spy II'' Review|journal=The Australian Commodore Review|volume=2|issue=7|page=6|publisher=Saturday Magazine Pty|issn=0816-5874|oclc=217544012}}</ref> Spies no longer start with a fixed number of traps but must collect the raw materials to build them

==Reception==
Steve Panak for ''[[ANALOG Computing]]'' wrote "you've got an action-packed game. ''Spy vs Spy II'' is a fantasy adventure recommended for all who enjoy a little harmless espionage."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/analog-computing-magazine-44|title=Analog Computing Magazine Issue 44 (Parallel Interface)|date=July 22, 1986|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>

''[[Computer and Video Games]]'' stated "The cartoon graphics are every bit as good as on ''Spy vs Spy'' and, with seven levels of action, you'll find it a real challenge."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Computer_and_Video_Games_Issue_0048|title=Computer and Video Games Issue 0048|via=Internet Archive}}</ref>

In a 92/100 review, ''[[Zzap!64|Zzap!]]'' concluded "Fans of the original won't be disappointed."<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Zzap!64 |issue=6 | date=October 1985 |url=https://archive.org/details/Zzap_640006/page/112/mode/2up |title=Spy vs. Spy II |pages=112â€“113 |via=Internet Archive}}</ref>

